Skull Stripping â€“ Isolates the brain by removing non-brain tissues for accurate structural analysis.

Nonuniformity Correction â€“ Corrects uneven intensity in MRI scans for consistent brightness.

Tissue Classification â€“ Segments gray matter, white matter, and cerebrospinal fluid for detailed study.

Cerebrum Labeling â€“ Identifies and labels major brain regions for anatomical mapping.

Inner Cortical Mask â€“ Defines the gray-white matter boundary to support cortical thickness analysis.

Scrub Mask â€“ Removes noise and small artifacts to improve segmentation accuracy.

Topology Correction â€“ Fixes surface irregularities for continuous cortical modeling.

VMP Removal â€“ Eliminates unwanted vascular and peripheral signals for cleaner results.

Inner Cortical & Pial Surfaces â€“ Builds precise brain surface models for thickness and structure visualization.

Split Hemispheres â€“ Separates the brain into left and right hemispheres for regional analysis.

Cortical Thickness Estimation â€“ Measures cortical thickness to assess structural brain integrity.

Co-registration to Atlas â€“ Aligns subject data with a standard brain atlas for cross-subject comparison.

Labeling of Brain Surfaces â€“ Assigns standardized region labels for consistent interpretation.

