Identify Representative Volume â€“ Selects a reference volume for alignment and registration.

Motion Correction â€“ Adjusts for subject movement during fMRI acquisition.

Skull Stripping â€“ Removes non-brain regions for cleaner functional data.

Rigid Registration to T1w â€“ Aligns fMRI data with anatomical MRI for precise localization.

Spatial Smoothing â€“ Enhances signal-to-noise ratio for more reliable statistical analysis.

Grand Mean Scaling â€“ Normalizes signal intensity across the entire dataset.

Bandpass Filtering & Nuisance Regression â€“ Removes physiological noise and low-frequency drifts.

